✅ Simple Definition (Easy Language)

Amazon EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud) is a service from Amazon Web Services that lets you create virtual servers in the cloud.

👉 In simple words:
EC2 = a computer (server) on the internet that you can use anytime

🎯 Interview Answer (Short & Clear)

You can say:

“Amazon EC2 is a cloud computing service that provides scalable virtual servers. It allows users to run applications without managing physical hardware, and we can easily start, stop, and scale instances based on requirements.”

🧠 Key Points to Remember
EC2 = virtual machine (server)
Runs in the cloud (no physical system needed)
You can:
Start / Stop / Restart
Install software (like Nginx, Docker)
Choose OS (Linux, Windows)
Pay only for usage 💰
📦 Real-Life Example
Your laptop = physical computer
EC2 = online laptop/server
You connect using SSH and use it like your own system
💬 Interview Q&A

Q1: What is an EC2 instance?
👉 A virtual server running on EC2.

Q2: Why use EC2?
👉 To run applications without buying hardware.

Q3: What is AMI?
👉 A template used to launch EC2 (OS + software).

